'''Citizens for Europe''' is a [[nonprofit organization]] that was created by [[Europe|European]] civil society actors in order to give a voice to the [[Culture of Europe|European society]].<ref name="auto">{{cite web |url=http://specialelections2014.eu/civil-society-mobilizes/i-vote-for-europe-2/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-04-10 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140413123054/http://specialelections2014.eu/civil-society-mobilizes/i-vote-for-europe-2/ |archivedate=2014-04-13 |df= }}</ref> It aims to help connect and form alliances between European organizations in order to raise their profile in the media and carry more weight when dealing with political decision makers.

Citizens for Europe is geared around three general activities: Linking the European community, promoting its members activities and agenda, and promoting its own agenda.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://europarl.me/who|title=Who are we? - Hacking Democracy|website=europarl.me}}</ref> Its network is made up of over 400 European organizations,<ref name="auto"/> along with a multitude of individuals working across almost every European country.

Citizens for Europe is financed by the Charles Léopold Mayer Foundation for the Progress of Humankind, and has been since it was founded in 2007.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fph.ch/rubrique34.html|title=Fondation Charles Léopold Mayer pour le progrès de l'Homme|website=www.fph.ch}}</ref>

